Description: Fender 50s-style Telecaster put together with all genuine Fender parts: -- outstanding American Vintage series 52 neck and 58 bridge pickups. -- Mexican standard series gloss butterscotch body with nice grain pattern and factory shielding in pickup cavities. -- Fender American Vintage series bridge assembly and dome knobs. -- Neck is a rare one: from a made-in-Mexico Fender Classic Player Triple Telecaster: it has vintage frets but a comfortable 9.5 radius and a really nice gloss finish. Nice tight neck pocket with no gaps. -- Pickguard is Fender American Vintage series; I added the neck pickup adjustment height screws to the pickguard. Excellent-plus condition: no dings or scratches or fret wear. Low action. Not a heavy guitar, it is light to medium weight. I don't have a scale to give exact weight. Great vintage vibe and sound at a good price. Ready to plug in and play. Comes with a like-new Roadrunner gig bag with thick padding. Will ship to USA only.
Title: Fender 50s style Telecaster with American Vintage 52 + 58 reissue pickups exc++
